  sodium: 1300 mg
---

Wash and dry produce. Zest @mandarin orange{1} until you have ¼ tsp (1⁄3 tsp for 4 servings); peel and dice fruit into bite-size pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sesame dressing{1.5%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%tbsp}, and mandarin zest. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @cashews{1/2%cup}, @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), and @water{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP water for 4). Cook, stirring often, until water has evaporated and cashews are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a second small bowl. Wipe out #pan.

Pat @chicken{}(skin removed and patted dry) dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for cashews over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Remove from pan; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with paper towels. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for cashews over medium-high heat. Add @shrimp{10} and season with @garlic powder{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @spinach{5%oz}, @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz}, and half the mandarin with half the dressing.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide salad between #bowls{}. Top with chicken, candied cashews, and remaining mandarin. Drizzle with remaining dressing and serve.